[This is a work of fiction not related to any persons, organizations, places, events, or settings.]

4
00:00:42,610 --> 00:00:44,880
Wait!

5
00:00:44,880 --> 00:00:49,350
You're not going to draw a heart or anything like that, are you?

6
00:00:50,030 --> 00:00:52,430
We're not like that.

7
00:00:52,430 --> 00:00:56,250
How about a triangle? Or a square? Circle?

8
00:00:56,250 --> 00:00:58,020
A circle is nice.

9
00:00:58,020 --> 00:01:01,160
No. I want a heart.

10
00:01:02,010 --> 00:01:04,340
Do whatever you want.

11
00:01:04,340 --> 00:01:08,620
[Yeong Min ♡ Ji Hyeon]

12
00:01:08,620 --> 00:01:12,900
Seo Yeong Min! What are you doing here alone?

13
00:01:12,900 --> 00:01:15,810
Hello, Doctor.

14
00:01:15,810 --> 00:01:18,570
Why are you two here?

15
00:01:20,030 --> 00:01:24,590
I ate dinner with Miss So Ri, and then we came to take a walk.

16
00:01:28,660 --> 00:01:30,580
Doctor,

17
00:01:31,530 --> 00:01:35,550
are you free tonight by any chance?

18
00:01:35,550 --> 00:01:39,340
I asked him out before.

19
00:01:40,450 --> 00:01:42,570
My photo, show it to him!

20
00:01:42,570 --> 00:01:44,440
He'll say he knows me for sure.

21
00:01:44,440 --> 00:01:46,960
Doctor,

22
00:01:48,720 --> 00:01:51,990
do you know this woman by any chance?

23
00:01:56,080 --> 00:01:57,810
Yes.

24
00:01:57,810 --> 00:02:00,090
I do know this person.

25
00:02:01,300 --> 00:02:04,650
How do you know Kang Ji Hyeon!?

26
00:02:04,650 --> 00:02:10,110
She was my patient, but unfortunately, she passed away.

27
00:02:10,110 --> 00:02:13,200
She was a good and cheerful detective.

28
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:16,200
Why? What photo is it?

29
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:19,800
Oh? This was a patient who came to the emergency room after an accident.

30
00:02:23,300 --> 00:02:26,560
So I died in an accident.

31
00:02:27,310 --> 00:02:32,280
Was Kang Ji Hyeon a detective?

32
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:34,410
Detective.

33
00:02:34,410 --> 00:02:39,020
Why are you asking about this person?

34
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:47,330
I was cleaning up my mom's belongings and found this photo on her phone.

35
00:02:47,330 --> 00:02:50,010
I was just curious.

36
00:02:50,850 --> 00:02:55,560
Since you work at the hospital, you would've seen many people.

37
00:02:55,560 --> 00:03:00,970
I thought you might know her, so I asked.

38
00:03:02,420 --> 00:03:03,850
I see.

39
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:08,100
By the way, why are you at a place like this?

40
00:03:10,420 --> 00:03:12,080
Did you come alone?

41
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:13,680
What?

42
00:03:14,670 --> 00:03:16,940
Y-Yes.

43
00:03:16,940 --> 00:03:19,330
Oh, my Yeong Min.

44
00:03:19,330 --> 00:03:20,630
"My Yeong Min?"

45
00:03:20,630 --> 00:03:24,090
Did you get a virgin ghost attached to you or something?

46
00:03:24,940 --> 00:03:28,320
No matter how lonely you get, you shouldn't come to these places alone.

47
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:30,120
Okay?

48
00:03:36,540 --> 00:03:38,640
It's amazing that I was really a detective!

49
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:42,520
They said I was a real detective. A real detective!

50
00:03:44,440 --> 00:03:46,370
Doctor.

51
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:56,430
Did you date the person from the photo that I showed you earlier?

52
00:03:58,330 --> 00:03:59,800
No.

53
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:02,400
We weren't in any relationship.

54
00:04:04,620 --> 00:04:06,150
That's a relief.

55
00:04:06,150 --> 00:04:07,410
Excuse me?

56
00:04:07,410 --> 00:04:10,820
What? N-No, it's nothing.

57
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:13,400
Let's go, Miss So Ri.

58
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:14,650
Okay.

59
00:04:14,650 --> 00:04:17,650
Then what is the memory of me asking him out?

60
00:04:19,150 --> 00:04:21,270
Was I rejected?

61
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:27,360
No way.

62
00:04:30,830 --> 00:04:35,850
[Delivery Man]

63
00:04:35,850 --> 00:04:41,200
No wonder I'm so agile.
[Episode 7]

64
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:43,390
A detective.

65
00:04:43,390 --> 00:04:46,210
So cool!

66
00:04:47,170 --> 00:04:50,130
Not every detective is cool.

67
00:04:50,850 --> 00:04:52,420
You could've been a corrupt detective.

68
00:04:52,420 --> 00:04:56,160
A bad detective that takes money under the table from criminals.

69
00:04:56,160 --> 00:05:00,370
How dare you. Also, Dr. Kyu Jin said

70
00:05:00,370 --> 00:05:06,270
that I was a "very cheerful and very good detective."

71
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:13,380
And a detective that was rejected by Dr. Kyu Jin.

72
00:05:13,380 --> 00:05:18,400
Well, that! A mistake in my memory.

73
00:05:22,690 --> 00:05:25,670
Youngji High School Kendo beauty.

74
00:05:25,670 --> 00:05:29,530
And also Detective Kang Ji Hyeon.

75
00:05:48,310 --> 00:05:50,070
Head!

76
00:05:51,530 --> 00:05:54,020
So cool!

77
00:05:54,640 --> 00:05:56,590
Is he already asleep?

78
00:06:14,230 --> 00:06:17,130
What are you doing? Why are you surprised?

79
00:06:17,130 --> 00:06:21,920
I'm surprised because you came out of nowhere! I can't get used to this.

80
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:24,750
What are you looking at?

81
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:28,960
You were looking me up.

82
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:32,740
Well, well, keep going.

83
00:06:39,340 --> 00:06:40,920
There's nothing.

84
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:46,340
Wow, a detective died, but there isn't even one news article?

85
00:06:46,340 --> 00:06:49,140
Was I really that unimportant?

86
00:06:49,900 --> 00:06:54,500
Or maybe, look up "female detective death case."

87
00:06:56,420 --> 00:06:58,940
[Female detective death case]

88
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:01,290
[Four female detectives / The only detective family]

89
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:10,810
I guess we have no choice.

90
00:07:10,810 --> 00:07:15,760
If this is it, we'll have to go out in person.

91
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:18,700
How?

92
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:21,600
[Dongpa Police Station]

93
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:23,340
I heard that this woman was a detective.

94
00:07:23,340 --> 00:07:27,350
Could you tell me which police station she was with?

95
00:07:27,350 --> 00:07:30,630
Also, I would like to know the contact information of this person's family.

96
00:07:31,660 --> 00:07:32,400
[...safe country]

97
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:37,460
Why are you curious about Detective Kang Ji Hyeon?

98
00:07:37,460 --> 00:07:40,200
As you can see,

99
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:43,920
- this was taken on the day my mother died.
- What do you mean?

100
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:47,330
It's weird that we died on the same day!

101
00:07:47,330 --> 00:07:52,410
I'm curious about the relationship between the deceased detective and my mother.

102
00:07:52,410 --> 00:07:56,420
Mrs. Kim Jin Suk died from a hit-and-run accident, though.

103
00:07:57,150 --> 00:08:01,840
The criminal hasn't been caught yet, so how would you know if it was a hit-and-run accident or an intentional murder?

104
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:05,150
What are you planning to do by meeting the detective's family?

105
00:08:05,150 --> 00:08:07,150
I have things to ask.

106
00:08:07,860 --> 00:08:13,970
Why she died, and what relationship she had with my mother.

107
00:08:15,460 --> 00:08:22,110
We found that Detective Kang Ji Hyeon and Mrs. Kim Jin Suk knew each other as cab driver and cop.

108
00:08:22,110 --> 00:08:24,310
The two cases are not related,

109
00:08:24,310 --> 00:08:29,330
and the fact that they died on the same day is just a coincidence.

110
00:08:29,870 --> 00:08:35,880
So there's no reason for you to meet with Detective Kang Ji Hyeon's family.

111
00:08:36,930 --> 00:08:43,160
Also, Ms. Kang Ji Hyeon's family is finally getting over the grief.

112
00:08:43,160 --> 00:08:47,390
What are you trying to do by opening up fresh wounds?

113
00:08:48,970 --> 00:08:52,250
You can't give up. You have to find out.

114
00:08:53,380 --> 00:08:58,740
It's been four months since my mother died, and you still haven't been able to arrest the culprit.

115
00:08:58,740 --> 00:09:00,170
What have you been doing?

116
00:09:00,170 --> 00:09:04,360
What if my mother's case becomes a cold case?

117
00:09:04,360 --> 00:09:06,510
We're trying, so just–

118
00:09:06,510 --> 00:09:10,170
No. I don't trust you anymore.

119
00:09:10,170 --> 00:09:14,410
I'll arrest the culprit myself, so please

120
00:09:14,410 --> 00:09:17,720
give me her family's contact information.

121
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:27,830
Do you know this woman by any chance?

122
00:09:37,690 --> 00:09:39,120
- Miss So Ri,
- Yes?

123
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:40,900
About Yeong Min...

124
00:09:40,900 --> 00:09:42,370
Yes?

125
00:09:42,370 --> 00:09:47,010
How did he say he knew the detective from the photo?

126
00:09:47,010 --> 00:09:49,230
Did he say he dated her?

127
00:09:49,230 --> 00:09:52,270
He definitely said that he didn't know her

128
00:09:52,270 --> 00:09:55,100
because he saw the photo while cleaning up his mother's belongings.

129
00:09:55,100 --> 00:09:57,570
Oh, right. That's what it was.

130
00:09:57,570 --> 00:10:00,290
Yeong Min and I are childhood friends.

131
00:10:00,290 --> 00:10:01,920
We know everything about each other.

132
00:10:01,920 --> 00:10:03,520
I see.

133
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:06,000
He's forever single.

134
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:09,300
He never seriously dated anyone.

135
00:10:09,300 --> 00:10:11,340
So am I.

136
00:10:11,340 --> 00:10:12,950
Excuse me?

137
00:10:13,770 --> 00:10:17,250
Come on, no way!

138
00:10:17,250 --> 00:10:20,520
A catch like you? Why?

139
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:22,340
It's true.

140
00:10:32,620 --> 00:10:36,510
In the end, we learned nothing.

141
00:10:41,050 --> 00:10:46,710
Even so, we're certain that you were a detective,

142
00:10:46,710 --> 00:10:52,320
so if we keep looking into it, we'll be able to learn what happened to you.

143
00:10:53,380 --> 00:10:55,720
Don't be too disappointed.

144
00:10:58,360 --> 00:11:01,360
But the detective from earlier said

145
00:11:02,690 --> 00:11:04,500
that my family...

146
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:12,020
After my death, they're finally starting to get over the pain little by little,

147
00:11:12,020 --> 00:11:15,480
and if I appear in front of them in this form

148
00:11:16,540 --> 00:11:19,040
would that be the right thing to do?

149
00:11:27,170 --> 00:11:29,040
[If the family is harmonious, everything will turn out well.]

150
00:11:33,560 --> 00:11:36,810
[If the family is harmonious, everything will turn out well.]

151
00:11:36,810 --> 00:11:40,530
Is there any way that I could comfort her?

152
00:11:41,180 --> 00:11:44,610
[If the family is harmonious, everything will turn out well.]

153
00:11:54,390 --> 00:11:59,640
Also, Ms. Kang Ji Hyeon's family is finally getting over the grief.

154
00:12:07,380 --> 00:12:10,260
Let's go over the investigation's progress.

155
00:12:10,260 --> 00:12:14,470
Okay. Nurse Kim Hui Yeon, who was with Detective Kang Ji Hyeon,

156
00:12:14,470 --> 00:12:17,270
testified at the witness interview that

157
00:12:17,270 --> 00:12:21,260
she was at a convenience store at the time of the accident, proving her alibi.

158
00:12:21,260 --> 00:12:23,460
Furthermore, the P.I. Gu Bong,

159
00:12:23,460 --> 00:12:29,210
the phone he turned in at the witness interview turned out to be a burner phone after tracing the number that ordered the job,

160
00:12:29,210 --> 00:12:33,920
and a fake account deposited the money to his account as well.

161
00:12:36,640 --> 00:12:39,110
What about the photos he took for the job?

162
00:12:39,110 --> 00:12:41,940
He said that most of them were deleted, so he has none.

163
00:12:50,750 --> 00:12:55,310
There's a nurse named Kim Jeong Wu at Daehun Medical Center.

164
00:13:08,590 --> 00:13:11,120
Where is Do Kyu Jin?

165
00:13:16,610 --> 00:13:18,780
Oh my! Knife, knife, knife!

166
00:13:18,780 --> 00:13:20,420
What are you doing?

167
00:13:22,330 --> 00:13:24,430
- I'm going to kill you.
- Why are you doing this?

168
00:13:24,430 --> 00:13:26,030
Let go!

169
00:13:26,030 --> 00:13:28,210
What are you doing!? Are you crazy?

170
00:13:29,760 --> 00:13:32,540
This is all because of you!

171
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:39,520
Don't come close!

172
00:13:39,520 --> 00:13:41,890
Don't come close!

173
00:13:48,410 --> 00:13:51,330
- Doctor, are you okay?
- I'm okay.

174
00:13:59,340 --> 00:14:00,750
What do ghosts like?

175
00:14:00,750 --> 00:14:03,360
What are you talking about? There's no context.

176
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:07,100
So what I'm saying is...

177
00:14:07,100 --> 00:14:08,950
I told you to get rid of her, didn't I?

178
00:14:08,950 --> 00:14:10,800
You could really die!

179
00:14:10,800 --> 00:14:13,730
Just answer the question.

180
00:14:13,730 --> 00:14:15,270
You've totally fallen for her.

181
00:14:15,270 --> 00:14:17,710
That's exactly what being possessed by a ghost is.

182
00:14:17,710 --> 00:14:20,380
Right now, you're possessed by a ghost.

183
00:14:21,650 --> 00:14:25,920
- No, no. Maybe it's for the better.
- What do you mean?

184
00:14:25,920 --> 00:14:29,050
Maybe she'll be able to move on.

185
00:14:29,050 --> 00:14:30,780
Even if they don't fulfill their wishes,

186
00:14:30,780 --> 00:14:34,050
even if they don't resolve their grievances, there's a way to pass on.

187
00:14:41,510 --> 00:14:43,470
Even if it's a ghost that has deep grievances,

188
00:14:43,470 --> 00:14:47,600
they could pass on if love sprouts within their hearts.

189
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:50,600
I can't let her go like this.

190
00:14:50,600 --> 00:14:52,420
No, it can't happen.

191
00:14:52,420 --> 00:14:56,470
I like you, Ms. Ji Hyeon.

192
00:14:57,810 --> 00:14:59,400
You can't.

193
00:15:01,010 --> 00:15:02,350
You can't like me.

194
00:15:02,350 --> 00:15:05,980
What kind of future

195
00:15:05,980 --> 00:15:08,360
or happiness would you have from liking me?

196
00:15:10,190 --> 00:15:11,480
It'll just hurt you.

197
00:15:11,480 --> 00:15:15,120
That's why Ms. Ji Hyeon put up a wall.

198
00:15:15,120 --> 00:15:17,650
She already knew.

199
00:15:17,650 --> 00:15:22,440
That if she falls in love, that she would pass on.

200
00:15:24,010 --> 00:15:26,380
I need to hide it.

201
00:15:26,380 --> 00:15:29,760
The fact that I like Ms. Ji Hyeon, my feelings.

202
00:15:29,760 --> 00:15:33,030
I need to hide it all. For Ms. Ji Hyeon.

203
00:15:38,080 --> 00:15:39,980
I can do it.

204
00:15:44,930 --> 00:15:46,670
Are you okay?

205
00:15:46,670 --> 00:15:48,550
I was just grazed.

206
00:15:48,550 --> 00:15:52,230
Do you know why nurse Kim Jeong Wu did that?

207
00:15:52,230 --> 00:15:57,470
It seems like wasn't happy about being fired.

208
00:15:57,470 --> 00:16:00,540
What was the reason for firing him?

209
00:16:00,540 --> 00:16:04,790
I fired him because it was discovered that he was stealing hospital drugs.

210
00:16:04,790 --> 00:16:08,560
I think he was waving around a weapon due to resentment toward me.

211
00:16:11,330 --> 00:16:14,950
What kind of drugs?

212
00:16:16,020 --> 00:16:18,550
General anesthetics.

213
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:36,380
Detective.

214
00:16:37,140 --> 00:16:39,290
Yes, nurse Kim Hui Yeon?

215
00:16:39,290 --> 00:16:41,900
Well,

216
00:16:43,140 --> 00:16:45,210
to tell you the truth,

217
00:16:45,210 --> 00:16:50,580
during the interview, I was thinking about whether or not I should've told you,

218
00:16:50,580 --> 00:16:55,850
and I believed that it didn't have anything to do with Detective Kang, so I didn't tell you.

219
00:17:00,130 --> 00:17:05,520
Nurse Kim Jeong Wu, he was a bit off.

220
00:17:12,530 --> 00:17:16,670
Could you tell us in detail what you're saying?

221
00:17:17,910 --> 00:17:21,430
He was never ordinary in his actions,

222
00:17:21,430 --> 00:17:23,960
but what was even more strange,

223
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:26,860
after Nurse Kim Jeong Wu came to our hospital,

224
00:17:26,860 --> 00:17:31,420
the number of patients that died in the emergency room increased dramatically.

225
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:51,370
- Nurse Kim?
- Yes?

226
00:17:51,370 --> 00:17:55,110
It looked like you were speaking to the detective.

227
00:17:55,110 --> 00:17:56,490
What were you talking about?

228
00:17:56,490 --> 00:17:58,850
I told them about nurse Kim Jeong Wu.

229
00:17:58,850 --> 00:18:03,610
That I'm suspicious because the number of deceased patients increased after Nurse Kim arrived.

230
00:18:03,610 --> 00:18:06,180
You should be letting the police know since it's true.

231
00:18:06,930 --> 00:18:08,750
That was a good call.

232
