Grandma.

239
00:18:38,310 --> 00:18:41,920
Oh. Yeong Min.

240
00:18:43,470 --> 00:18:45,540
What are you doing here?

241
00:18:45,540 --> 00:18:48,080
It's.. I-I'm...

242
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:50,050
I asked what you're doing!

243
00:18:50,050 --> 00:18:53,210
Why are you yelling!? You'll scare the children.

244
00:18:53,210 --> 00:18:58,150
- Grandma.
- I'm working at my part-time job.

245
00:18:58,150 --> 00:19:00,560
Why are you working part time?

246
00:19:00,560 --> 00:19:03,480
What if your health gets worse doing this?

247
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:07,990
I'm busy right now. Let's talk later at home.

248
00:19:09,840 --> 00:19:11,810
Grandma.

249
00:19:11,810 --> 00:19:14,320
You shouldn't do this at someone's job.

250
00:19:14,320 --> 00:19:17,250
I said let's talk later at home.

251
00:19:38,620 --> 00:19:40,200
He should just get back in.

252
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:43,410
You may cross. Raise your hand.

253
00:19:46,350 --> 00:19:49,030
- Quit immediately.
- No.

254
00:19:49,030 --> 00:19:51,350
What if you faint again?

255
00:19:51,350 --> 00:19:54,220
I won't. I'm healthy!

256
00:19:54,220 --> 00:19:56,530
Grandma, are you dating someone?

257
00:19:58,400 --> 00:19:59,800
What are you talking about? Out of the blue.

258
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:02,000
Earlier, that grandpa that was in front of you.

259
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:04,680
Aren't you acting like this because of the hot grandpa?

260
00:20:04,680 --> 00:20:09,900
I'm asking if he's the reason why you dress up and go out early in the morning!

261
00:20:12,410 --> 00:20:14,770
Yes. That's right.

262
00:20:14,770 --> 00:20:18,890
Why? Can't old people go on dates?

263
00:20:18,890 --> 00:20:21,450
[If the family is harmonious, everything will turn out well.]

264
00:20:25,110 --> 00:20:27,480
Okay. I'll quit.

265
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:30,150
I'll quit, okay?

266
00:20:30,150 --> 00:20:31,950
[If the family is harmonious, everything will turn out well.]

267
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:36,030
Are you a child?

268
00:20:36,030 --> 00:20:39,230
Why are you throwing a tantrum?

269
00:20:39,230 --> 00:20:42,840
This is all because of money, because of the debt.

270
00:20:42,840 --> 00:20:46,780
That's why grandma is working part time, even though she's not in the best of health.

271
00:20:46,780 --> 00:20:51,040
Is there a lot left?

272
00:20:51,040 --> 00:20:55,790
I paid back the interest for now. I put out the urgent fire, but

273
00:20:55,790 --> 00:20:59,270
I have a long way to go if I want to pay back the entire amount.

274
00:21:11,020 --> 00:21:14,530
Should we make the ghost taxi business hours longer?

275
00:21:20,350 --> 00:21:24,430
How can we increase the income for the ghost taxi?

276
00:21:26,770 --> 00:21:29,070
Should we try a bargain sale?

277
00:21:29,070 --> 00:21:32,680
[Soul release service bargain sale]

278
00:21:32,680 --> 00:21:38,000
Those who can't pass on yet, please come and gather here.

279
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:41,560
Yes, right here.

280
00:21:43,970 --> 00:21:45,940
Hello.

281
00:21:47,760 --> 00:21:50,460
Why weren't you able to pass on?

282
00:21:50,460 --> 00:21:51,860
Your grievances,

283
00:21:51,860 --> 00:21:57,180
if you tell us your reasons, we will resolve all of them for you.

284
00:21:57,180 --> 00:21:58,340
[Soul release service bargain sale]

285
00:21:58,340 --> 00:22:01,620
No, no. I don't think that's a good idea.

286
00:22:03,160 --> 00:22:06,930
Then maybe we only take reservations?

287
00:22:06,930 --> 00:22:09,240
(Appointments in September)

288
00:22:09,240 --> 00:22:12,090
One, two, three, four, five.

289
00:22:12,090 --> 00:22:14,840
Our schedule is full.

290
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:26,310
[Money road instead of flower road]

291
00:22:27,360 --> 00:22:29,880
This isn't it either.

292
00:22:30,770 --> 00:22:34,770
The time frame for granting wishes is so unpredictable.

293
00:22:38,710 --> 00:22:42,630
Grandma, good morning.

294
00:22:45,780 --> 00:22:49,550
You must be getting breakfast ready.

295
00:22:51,220 --> 00:22:54,360
My grandson goes to work early in the morning.

296
00:22:54,360 --> 00:22:58,970
I will make sure he has a hearty meal before going to work.

297
00:22:59,820 --> 00:23:04,020
Why would you take care of a grandson who gets angry at you?

298
00:23:05,350 --> 00:23:07,810
He must've felt frustrated, too.

299
00:23:07,810 --> 00:23:09,420
After seeing me work,

300
00:23:09,420 --> 00:23:12,870
his heart must've dropped thinking I might faint again.

301
00:23:12,870 --> 00:23:14,640
That's right.

302
00:23:14,640 --> 00:23:20,030
If something happens to you, Yeong Min would have a really hard time.

303
00:23:20,030 --> 00:23:24,520
That's why he was angry, so try to understand him.

304
00:23:24,520 --> 00:23:28,720
Well that's why I'm telling him to meet a good partner!

305
00:23:28,720 --> 00:23:32,180
Why can't he date like everyone else?

306
00:23:34,680 --> 00:23:38,740
I need to make sure he has a good partner.

307
00:23:38,740 --> 00:23:41,920
Then can I leave peacefully.

308
00:23:45,730 --> 00:23:47,580
Come on.

309
00:24:08,770 --> 00:24:13,310
I'm sorry about getting upset yesterday.

310
00:24:13,310 --> 00:24:15,030
It's all right.

311
00:24:15,030 --> 00:24:17,670
I know how you feel.

312
00:24:17,670 --> 00:24:21,140
I know that you said all that because you worry about me.

313
00:24:21,140 --> 00:24:23,520
Of course, I know that.

314
00:24:24,220 --> 00:24:26,020
Grandma.

315
00:24:27,330 --> 00:24:30,290
So don't worry about it.

316
00:24:30,290 --> 00:24:32,590
You must be hungry. Sit.

317
00:24:32,590 --> 00:24:34,340
Let's eat breakfast.

318
00:24:34,340 --> 00:24:35,930
Okay.

319
00:25:12,790 --> 00:25:14,710
It's good.

320
00:25:15,600 --> 00:25:17,540
Eat up.

321
00:25:28,860 --> 00:25:31,270
Good morning!

322
00:25:31,270 --> 00:25:32,940
Good mor–

323
00:25:35,580 --> 00:25:39,410
What is this? Why are you stopping mid-sentence?

324
00:25:39,410 --> 00:25:43,620
We see each other every day. Why the greeting suddenly?

325
00:25:45,760 --> 00:25:50,290
Even if it's a ghost that has deep grievances, they could pass on

326
00:25:50,290 --> 00:25:52,410
if love sprouts within their hearts.

327
00:26:08,380 --> 00:26:10,660
Wh-What about me? What about me? Me?!

328
00:26:10,660 --> 00:26:13,110
I'm sorry, Ms. Ji Hyeon.

329
00:26:14,010 --> 00:26:16,200
Be by yourself today.

330
00:26:16,200 --> 00:26:18,360
Grandma!

331
00:26:18,360 --> 00:26:22,340
Yeong Min left me alone and went off again!

332
00:26:22,340 --> 00:26:26,140
Seriously, I don't know why your grandson is like that these days.

333
00:26:26,140 --> 00:26:28,180
Someone's calling you.

334
00:26:37,340 --> 00:26:39,540
Hello?

335
00:26:40,480 --> 00:26:43,900
From now on,

336
00:26:43,900 --> 00:26:47,650
I don't think I can work part-time.

337
00:26:47,650 --> 00:26:52,410
My bratty grandson is worried about me.

338
00:26:54,220 --> 00:26:59,950
Yes. Thank you for taking good care of me until now.

339
00:27:00,670 --> 00:27:02,280
Yes, yes.

340
00:27:02,280 --> 00:27:04,750
Please take care then.

341
00:27:08,760 --> 00:27:11,000
Is it the grandpa from that time?

342
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:15,560
Even if you quit the part-time job, go on dates with him and stuff.

343
00:27:15,560 --> 00:27:17,750
He's good looking.

344
00:27:25,630 --> 00:27:26,670
You're going to Samgam-dong, right?

345
00:27:26,670 --> 00:27:28,360
Yes.
[Reserved]

346
00:27:29,210 --> 00:27:31,930
What is this? A ride share?

347
00:27:31,930 --> 00:27:34,270
Are some taxis still doing ride shares these days?

348
00:27:34,270 --> 00:27:38,820
Sir, this person is not a customer, but my mother.

349
00:27:38,820 --> 00:27:39,980
Mother?

350
00:27:39,980 --> 00:27:44,060
My mother has Alzheimer's, so I travel with her.

351
00:27:44,060 --> 00:27:46,940
Thank you for your understanding.

352
00:27:46,940 --> 00:27:48,470
[Notice: The person in the passenger seat is my mother, who has Alzheimer's. Thank you for understanding. ]

353
00:27:48,470 --> 00:27:51,220
That driver who goes around with her mother who has Alzheimer's?

354
00:27:51,220 --> 00:27:53,450
I think I saw it on TV too.

355
00:27:53,450 --> 00:27:56,610
Yes, thank you for understanding.

356
00:27:58,610 --> 00:28:00,910
This is why people need to die when they get old.

357
00:28:00,910 --> 00:28:06,480
An old person who lost their mind is blocking their child's future.

358
00:28:06,480 --> 00:28:08,780
It's a curse. A curse.

359
00:28:08,780 --> 00:28:14,230
The Goryeojang from olden times needs to come back,
(T/N: A tradition of abandoning elderly parents in the mountain.)

360
00:28:14,230 --> 00:28:18,580
so we can legally dump useless elders.

361
00:28:27,330 --> 00:28:28,260
Please get out.

362
00:28:28,260 --> 00:28:30,520
"Get out"? We're not at the destination!

363
00:28:30,520 --> 00:28:35,090
I can't drive a customer like you, so get out!

364
00:28:37,250 --> 00:28:40,300
What? Living long is a curse?

365
00:28:40,300 --> 00:28:41,990
Do you think you won't get old?

366
00:28:41,990 --> 00:28:44,800
Everyone gets old!

367
00:28:44,800 --> 00:28:46,580
You're refusing a customer.

368
00:28:46,580 --> 00:28:51,590
I don't care. Get the hell out of my car.

369
00:28:53,730 --> 00:28:55,990
Get out!

370
00:28:59,270 --> 00:29:01,010
Who's in charge here?

371
00:29:01,010 --> 00:29:03,730
Get the boss out here!

372
00:29:03,730 --> 00:29:05,600
It's okay.

373
00:29:07,870 --> 00:29:11,460
Eun Su, are you okay?

374
00:29:11,460 --> 00:29:13,370
Seok Jin.

375
00:29:14,120 --> 00:29:17,100
Who are you? Are you this woman's husband?

376
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:21,650
My grandfather is the chairman of Heukun Transport.

377
00:29:23,100 --> 00:29:24,470
I'm going to sue this woman.

378
00:29:24,470 --> 00:29:29,290
She refused service, ride shared, and on top of that, an important business meeting was ruined thanks to this woman.

379
00:29:29,290 --> 00:29:31,390
Do you know how much I lost?

380
00:29:31,390 --> 00:29:34,510
I'm going to claim damages, so watch out.

381
00:29:34,510 --> 00:29:36,300
Understood?

382
00:29:38,170 --> 00:29:44,180
Sue, claim for damages, do all you want.

383
00:29:44,910 --> 00:29:48,350
- What?
- I saw the dash cam footage from the taxi.

384
00:29:48,350 --> 00:29:53,320
Your wise, immortal words were no joke.

385
00:29:54,100 --> 00:29:58,770
I'm planning on posting that on social media.

386
00:29:59,690 --> 00:30:03,150
- What?
- If I did, you'd be the national asshole in the blink of an eye.

387
00:30:03,150 --> 00:30:07,190
"Don't you have parents?" "Do you think you won't age for thousands and millions of years?"

388
00:30:08,210 --> 00:30:10,510
I can already see the comments.

389
00:30:11,680 --> 00:30:13,170
Did you say you run a business?

390
00:30:13,170 --> 00:30:17,500
If your identity was discovered, and they start boycotting, oh boy.

391
00:30:17,500 --> 00:30:20,770
The business meeting being ruined will be nothing.

392
00:30:21,860 --> 00:30:24,840
Your whole business would be ruined.

393
00:30:35,810 --> 00:30:36,830
Yes, yes.

394
00:30:36,830 --> 00:30:39,700
Thank you for understanding with a big heart.

395
00:30:40,320 --> 00:30:42,660
I'm really sorry.

396
00:30:46,850 --> 00:30:48,470
It's already so late.

397
00:30:48,470 --> 00:30:50,150
I need to get going.

398
00:30:50,150 --> 00:30:51,920
Take care.

399
00:30:59,810 --> 00:31:02,370
Ma'am, you must be hungry.

400
00:31:03,530 --> 00:31:05,730
Let's go eat.

401
00:31:07,540 --> 00:31:09,430
Mom, what do you want to eat?

402
00:31:09,430 --> 00:31:11,960
Maybe your favorite, meat?

403
00:31:11,960 --> 00:31:14,830
[GB Private Investigator]

404
00:31:21,470 --> 00:31:23,420
Please come in.

405
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:36,080
How can I help you?

406
00:31:44,210 --> 00:31:45,570
What's this?

407
00:31:45,570 --> 00:31:49,550
Do you know the woman on the left by any chance?

408
00:31:51,650 --> 00:31:53,350
Why?

409
00:31:53,870 --> 00:31:57,070
Who the hell are you?

410
00:31:58,340 --> 00:32:00,740
I can't reach my friend.

411
00:32:00,740 --> 00:32:05,330
This office was the last place she told me she was coming to.

412
00:32:06,160 --> 00:32:08,310
This is annoying me again.

413
00:32:08,950 --> 00:32:14,960
Hey, do you know how often I had to go in and out of the police station because of this woman?

414
00:32:15,460 --> 00:32:18,970
This woman is dead. She's dead.

415
00:32:20,500 --> 00:32:22,080
What did you say? Is she dead?

416
00:32:22,080 --> 00:32:23,920
I don't know; I don't. So are you going to make a request?

417
00:32:23,920 --> 00:32:26,140
You won't, right? Then leave.

418
00:32:26,140 --> 00:32:30,320
Then do you know anything about this woman's family?

419
00:32:30,320 --> 00:32:33,500
Get out. I'm not joking. Get out.

420
00:32:33,500 --> 00:32:35,820
Please, just once, tell me! Please?

421
00:32:35,820 --> 00:32:38,210
Get out, right now.

422
00:33:06,900 --> 00:33:09,230
[Detective Kang Hyeong Su]

423
00:33:09,230 --> 00:33:12,210
Detective Kang Ji Hyeon.

424
00:33:19,860 --> 00:33:21,640
How can I help?

425
00:33:21,640 --> 00:33:25,420
Perhaps your wife is having an affair.

426
00:33:26,690 --> 00:33:30,990
I'm Detective Kang Hyeong Su from the Bukdaemun police station.

427
00:33:30,990 --> 00:33:34,730
I'm the father of Detective Kang Ji Hyeon.

428
00:33:35,770 --> 00:33:40,700
I heard from my daughter that you took photos of the bereaved family.

429
00:33:40,700 --> 00:33:43,050
I want those photos.

430
00:33:43,860 --> 00:33:48,680
Detective, I'm sorry, but I can't.

431
00:33:48,680 --> 00:33:52,450
I don't reveal the privacy of customers.

432
00:33:52,450 --> 00:33:54,870
Even if I didn't have to deal with that bullshit,

433
00:33:54,870 --> 00:33:58,080
I delete old files.

434
00:33:58,080 --> 00:34:00,590
Do you expect me to believe that?

435
00:34:00,590 --> 00:34:04,270
I know people like you.

436
00:34:04,270 --> 00:34:09,030
Okay. You may reveal it or not. However...

437
00:34:09,030 --> 00:34:13,600
beware that revealing the photo is the only way for you to live.

438
00:34:14,530 --> 00:34:17,350
That customer of yours,

439
00:34:17,350 --> 00:34:20,470
do you think they'll let you live?

440
00:34:20,470 --> 00:34:23,850
When they know you have those photos?

441
00:34:35,240 --> 00:34:38,550
This is the chart of deceased patients from the emergency room of Daehun Medical Center.

442
00:34:40,410 --> 00:34:43,900
What are all these random memories?

443
00:34:44,920 --> 00:34:47,580
But one thing is certain.

444
00:34:52,290 --> 00:34:53,970
What's up?

445
00:34:53,970 --> 00:34:57,130
I have something to ask you.

446
00:34:57,130 --> 00:34:59,090
- Detective Kang Ji Hyeon.
- Yes?

447
00:34:59,090 --> 00:35:01,510
She died in an accident, right?

448
00:35:01,510 --> 00:35:04,440
Can you tell me how she passed away?

449
00:35:05,250 --> 00:35:09,270
Why are you trying to find that out?

450
00:35:09,270 --> 00:35:14,440
In case it's related to my mother's death.

451
00:35:15,960 --> 00:35:18,580
She came to the emergency room in an ambulance.

452
00:35:18,580 --> 00:35:23,200
She was treated urgently and moved to the ICU, but she passed away suddenly.

453
00:35:23,200 --> 00:35:25,280
A cardiac arrest.

454
00:35:26,080 --> 00:35:27,850
But

455
00:35:27,850 --> 00:35:34,980
is there really a connection between your mother's death and Kang Ji Hyeon's?

456
00:35:34,980 --> 00:35:37,300
I don't know yet.

457
00:35:38,480 --> 00:35:41,420
Thanks for helping anyway.

458
00:35:41,420 --> 00:35:45,400
Of course, I should help. We're friends like that.

459
00:35:45,400 --> 00:35:51,670
Then could I maybe get Detective Kang Ji Hyeon's family's contact info?

460
00:35:51,670 --> 00:35:56,970
I don't know it; even if I did, I can't leak a patient's information.

461
00:35:56,970 --> 00:35:58,380
Come on!

462
00:35:58,380 --> 00:36:00,370
Never.

463
00:36:11,540 --> 00:36:15,780
Nurse Kim Jeong Wu's address was this studio apartment.

464
00:36:16,340 --> 00:36:21,090
It could be because it's a studio apartment where a lot of Daehun's staff members live,

465
00:36:21,090 --> 00:36:23,810
but nurse Kim Hui Yeon and nurse Kim Jeong Wu...

466
00:36:23,810 --> 00:36:30,290
Also, the case where Mrs. Kim Jin Suk died in a hit-and-run accident in front of here,

467
00:36:30,290 --> 00:36:34,050
there seems to be something.

468
00:36:34,600 --> 00:36:36,180
Let's go check it out anyway.

469
00:36:36,180 --> 00:36:37,730
Sure.

470
00:36:49,190 --> 00:36:51,720
I don't think anyone is home.

471
00:36:51,720 --> 00:36:54,800
You have Kim Jeong Wu's phone number, right? Call him.

472
00:36:54,800 --> 00:36:56,370
Okay.

473
00:36:57,590 --> 00:36:59,840
Mr. Kim Jeong Wu?

474
00:37:00,460 --> 00:37:02,640
His phone is off too.

475
00:37:04,060 --> 00:37:06,550
Mr. Kim Jeong Wu, are you home?

476
00:37:07,930 --> 00:37:10,970
Mr. Kim Jeong Wu, are you there?

477
00:37:27,990 --> 00:37:32,140
What do you think you're doing?

478
00:37:32,140 --> 00:37:36,310
Why on earth did you leave the phone at home?

479
00:37:39,990 --> 00:37:44,510
Mister Driver, did I upset you?

480
00:37:44,510 --> 00:37:47,130
Why are you suddenly being like this?

481
00:37:47,790 --> 00:37:50,720
I had an urgent matter to attend to. That's why.

482
00:37:51,450 --> 00:37:53,280
I'm sorry.

483
00:37:54,340 --> 00:37:58,590
I'm the sales manager of this ghost taxi.

484
00:37:58,590 --> 00:38:02,530
How could you leave without me?

485
00:38:02,530 --> 00:38:05,170
Well, if I have urgent business...

486
00:38:05,170 --> 00:38:08,440
Why are you nagging me so much?

487
00:38:13,530 --> 00:38:16,280
"Nagging"?

488
00:38:16,280 --> 00:38:19,130
How can he forget?

489
00:38:19,900 --> 00:38:22,910
I can't stand it; I'll kill him.

490
00:38:28,670 --> 00:38:32,070
I've been thinking all day long,

491
00:38:32,070 --> 00:38:37,790
and I don't know exactly what the fragments of my memories are trying to tell me,

492
00:38:37,790 --> 00:38:41,300
but the memories have something in common.

493
00:38:41,300 --> 00:38:43,250
What is it?

494
00:38:44,530 --> 00:38:46,580
Daehun Medical Center.

495
00:38:48,210 --> 00:38:53,950
I don't know what it is, but I think we might be able to find a hint if we go to the hospital.

496
00:38:53,950 --> 00:38:57,390
So let's go to the hospital right now.

497
00:39:00,870 --> 00:39:03,520
Let's go later. I'm tired.

498
00:39:03,520 --> 00:39:06,620
My body feels heavy.

499
00:39:06,620 --> 00:39:08,490
We need to quickly look into it!

500
00:39:08,490 --> 00:39:10,850
Let's go now.

501
00:39:11,360 --> 00:39:14,850
I don't even have the energy to lift a finger.

502
00:39:14,850 --> 00:39:15,980
Mister Driver.

503
00:39:15,980 --> 00:39:20,600
Do you know how exhausting it is to deal with ghosts all day?

504
00:39:20,600 --> 00:39:23,220
Why are you pushing me so hard?

505
00:39:47,750 --> 00:39:49,780
Ms. Ji Hyeon, are you crying?

506
00:39:49,780 --> 00:39:52,040
I'm pissed!

507
00:39:52,040 --> 00:39:53,850
[Daehun Medical Center]

508
00:40:02,490 --> 00:40:03,940
[Blood Collection Room]

509
00:40:03,940 --> 00:40:07,940
What is this? You said we'd come here later since you're so tired.

510
00:40:07,940 --> 00:40:13,130
Well, you were crying.

511
00:40:13,130 --> 00:40:16,600
Anyone would be upset in that situation!

512
00:40:16,600 --> 00:40:18,440
I'm sorry.

513
00:40:18,440 --> 00:40:20,320
Please calm down.

514
00:40:24,940 --> 00:40:26,620
Mr. Yeong Min.

515
00:40:26,670 --> 00:40:30,150
Oh.

516
00:40:30,150 --> 00:40:31,230
Dr. Do Kyu Jin.

517
00:40:31,230 --> 00:40:32,290
Doctor!

518
00:40:32,290 --> 00:40:34,490
What are you doing here at this time?

519
00:40:34,490 --> 00:40:36,160
Is your grandma sick?

520
00:40:36,160 --> 00:40:38,390
N-No.

521
00:40:38,390 --> 00:40:43,680
My colleague said their family member was admitted to the hospital.

522
00:40:43,680 --> 00:40:45,750
Doctor, I heard you were hurt.

523
00:40:45,750 --> 00:40:48,040
Are you feeling okay?

524
00:40:48,040 --> 00:40:49,780
